Preheat the #oven to 400 degrees.

> If you have a grill, both the steak and the nectarines can be cooked there so fire it up!

Thinly slice the @basil{1%bunch} leaves.

Halve and pit the @nectarine{2%unit}, then thinly slice into wedges.

Mince the @shallot{1%unit}.

Heat @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat.

Season the @sirloin steak{12%ounce} on all sides with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Sear the steak for ~{3-4%minutes} per side, until golden brown.

Transfer to a #baking sheet{} and finish cooking in the oven for ~{5-7%minutes}, or until
cooked to desired doneness.

Let the steak rest for ~{5%minutes}.

Char the nectarines: add the nectarines to the same pan over high heat.

Sear ~{1-2%minutes} per side, or until caramelized and charred.

Set aside.

== Vinaigrette ==

Make the vinaigrette: in a large #bowl{}, whisk together the shallot, @red wine vinegar{2%tablespoon},
and @olive oil{1 1/2%tablespoons}.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Thinly slice the steak against the grain.

Toss the @mixed greens{4%ounce} and basil into the vinaigrette.

Top with the steak, nectarines, @feta cheese{1%ounce}, and @pecans{1%ounce}.

Enjoy!